​Corruption poses significant challenges to both national and international governance, economic development, and social justice. To combat this issue, countries worldwide have implemented various anti-corruption policies and frameworks. Below is an overview of India's anti-corruption measures, followed by a discussion of anti-corruption policies in other countries.​

Anti-Corruption Policies in India
India has established a comprehensive legal and institutional framework to address corruption, primarily through the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (PCA).​
